Q:

Django template tags and tags function

I want to iterate over dictionary's tags but tags function gives me only first tag.
{% for tag in post.tags if tag.name_tag %}
    {% if tag.name_tag == "1" %}
       <p>
         <br>Tag: {{ tag.name_tag }}
       </p>
    {% endif %}
   {% endfor %}
{% endfor %}

A:

I can see that you can use it by adding {% get_tags for post %}
But the solution I give below is simpler:
{% if post.meta.tags %}
    {% for tag in post.meta.tags limit 0 10 %}
      <p>
        <br>Tag: {{ tag.name_tag }}
      </p>
    {% endfor %}
{% endif %}

