I am implementing app using xcode. I have two device types iPhones, and iPads. I need to test in iPad. In xcode simulator, by default, it will show both screen sizes. I want to make sure to use proper screen size for iPad in code when testing. My main.storyboard is same as iphone but for UI and size, its different for iPad. So can I test code on different devices by using one storyboard? 
What should I do for testing iPad size and size at a time for testing?

A:

In view controller for iPad, use below code
    if([[[UIDevice currentDevice] systemVersion] floatValue] < 8.0)
    {
        self.edgesForExtendedLayout = UIRectEdgeNone;
    }
    else
    {
        // Set the edge of the view controller's extended layout
        // to the edges to be kept
        self.edgesForExtendedLayout = UIRectEdgeNone;
    }

